rows.label: tev018401_MSG0001
rows.name:
Mira right now is kinda like San Francisco before
the gold rush.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0002
rows.name:
We know there are valuable resources all around us,
but most of them haven't been claimed yet.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0003
rows.name:
While the rest of BLADE is off casually performing
missions, I'm gonna expand FrontierNav and make
a fortune![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0004
rows.name:
Do you wanna get in on this action?
If so, I'm gonna need every last credit you got.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0005
rows.name:
Oh, and you'll only be a junior partner,
so you have to follow orders from me.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0010
rows.name:
I hear that goody-goody Kirsty is going around to
BLADEs who ain't been clued in yet and teaching 'em
all about FrontierNav.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0011
rows.name:
Why can't she mind her own damn business, huh?
What if one of those little pukes beats me to a prime
FrontierNav spot and installs a probe?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0012
rows.name:
And if she's such a freakin' expert, why doesn't she
go get rich herself instead of shooting her mouth
off about it to everyone else?![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0018
rows.name:
If you spot a scenic viewpoint or unexplored territory
while you're out gallivanting around, you better make
sure I'm the first one you tell![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0019
rows.name: ...Huh? What's my interest in those?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0020
rows.name:
Money, ya dolt! What, ya think I actually like staring
at nature-y crap all day? Pfffft.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0021
rows.name:
You set a research probe at a scenic viewpoint or
unexplored territory, and everyone logs on to check the
view out. Then I...er, WE pocket the ad revenue![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0022
rows.name:
Here on Mira, a nice view could be worth more than
any gemstone or precious metal.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0027
rows.name:
...Me? Well let me ask you this—what good would
a washed-up engineer-turned-Pathfinder like me be at
a time like that?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0028
rows.name:
Not much, right? So while you were stompin' around
New LA firing guns in the air like a damn fool,
I was looking for more unexplored territories to exploit![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0029
rows.name:
In fact, I found a real special beach at the foot of those
cliffs in Noctilum.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0030
rows.name:
Sure am glad I got out when I did.
Sounds like that battle was a real nasty one.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0035
rows.name:
Have you heard about what's at the very tippy-top of
Mount M'gando in the northern part of Cauldros?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0036
rows.name:
Well, I have! And I hear it's a uniquely beautiful hot
spring where the area's nastiest monsters live.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0037
rows.name:
Sounds like a spot like that could be worth big bucks,
yeah?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0038
rows.name:
But that mountain's way too dangerous.
Even I ain't that greedy.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG0039
rows.name:
Now if YOU want to take a shot at it, be my guest!
Just make sure to transfer your life savings to my
account first. I'll take care of it when you're dead.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2001
rows.name:
Have you heard about what's at the very tippy-top of
Mount M'gando in the northern part of Cauldros?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2002
rows.name:
Well, I have! And I hear it's a uniquely beautiful hot
spring where the area's nastiest monsters live.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2003
rows.name:
Sounds like a spot like that could be worth big bucks,
yeah?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2004
rows.name:
But that mountain's way too dangerous.
Even I ain't that greedy.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2005
rows.name: Still, I bet you could pull it off. Just be careful up there.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2010
rows.name:
Lately I've been busy looking for something,
and I had to prioritize that over installing data probes.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2011
rows.name: ...Huh? You wanna know what I was looking for?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG2012
rows.name:
Sorry, pal. Trade secret. Can't share that with no one.
Not even you.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3001
rows.name:
I know you wouldn't believe it lookin' at me now,
but before the accident I was a handsome, young
engineer who was popular with all the ladies.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3002
rows.name:
I spent two years on the White Whale,
working with the team that made FrontierNav.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3003
rows.name:
We finally got it finished—and yeah, I dunno if my
contributions ended up being worth much...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3004
rows.name:
But to this day, I'm proud to have been part of the
team that created it. That network found us the Lifehold
Core and secured humanity's future.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3009
rows.name:
We've been analyzing the data units our old teammates
left behind and using what we've learned to start
creating the next generation of FrontierNav.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3010
rows.name:
But this time, they had some crazy plan to make it an
intergalactic network! This is on a totally different scale
from what we were working on before...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3011
rows.name:
Still, Kirsty and I just sit at our terminals nodding and
mm-hmming as if we know what the hell we're doing.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3012
rows.name:
Those bastards sure left us with one hell of a parting
gift.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_MSG3013
rows.name:
I dunno how far we'll get, but even if it costs me every
penny in the bank and the rest of my life, I'm going to
make this happen.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev018401_SEL0081
rows.name: Ask about his time on the White Whale.
